column1: Phage ID: Include every Phage ELISA Positive well
Antigen A450 and PBSA450: Provide ELISA well values from Phage ELISA Experiment
Bleed Date: Na‹ve, Day 28, Day 49, Day 70
Library Lot Number: Enter Library Batch Number
Biopanning and Phage ELISA Experiment Numbers: Enter a reference to the Biopanning and Phage ELISA Experiment so that original data can be identified

Current Decision Options: Resequence, Ignore, Subclone, Dropped (Dropped = any circumstance after subcloning that the NBX is dropped, if this action is taken a note explaining the decisions must be included at the end of the line)
NBX Designation: Provide NBX Number or Not Applicable

Protein Sequence: Add amino acid sequence. If there are any "X" they should be highlighted in RED text. If sent for resequencing don't add any text. If subcloned, fix the the sequence but leave the text red

DNA Sequence: Add nucleotide sequence. If there are any "N" they should be highlighted in RED text. If sent for resequencing don't add any text. If subcloned, fix the the sequence but leave the text red
Sequencing Experiment: Provide a reference to the sequencing data deemed to be the final correct sequence for the antibody
CDR1, CDR2, CDR3: add amino acid sequences called by Nick's CDR output program. These should be checked by eye as error do occur. If there is any doubt please ask Slade.
CDR Family Members for Cloned NBXs: Enter all members from the llama that are in the same CDR family. Remove any NBXs with a current decision of "dropped"
